<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('./partials/head') -%>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>Exercise Tracker API</h1>
      <p>Created by <a href="https://autumnchris.github.io/portfolio" target="_blank">Autumn Bullard</a> &copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear(); %></p>
    </header>
    <main>
      <p>An Express.js API that creates a username and gets a list of exercises for that unique username as well as logs new exercises.</p>
      <p>View the <a href="https://github.com/autumnchris/exercise-tracker-api" target="_blank">source code</a> for this project.</p>
      <hr>
      <section>
        <h2>Submit Exercise Data</h2>
        <div class="subsection">
          <h3>Create a User</h3>
          <p>Create a username in the form below to get a unique user ID that you will use when logging new exercises.</p>
          <form class="new-user" action="/api/exercise/new-user" method="post">
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="user">Username*</label>
              <input type="text" name="newUser" id="user" required>
            </div>
            <input type="submit" class="button" value="Submit">
          </form>
        </div>
        <div class="subsection">
          <h3>Log an Exercise</h3>
          <p>Add an exercise in the form below using your unique user ID.</p>
          <form class="add-exercise" action="/api/exercise/add" method="post">
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="user-id">User ID*</label>
              <input type="text" name="userId" id="user-id" required>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="description">Description*</label>
              <input type="text" name="description" id="description" required>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="duration">Duration (in minutes)*</label>
              <input type="text" name="duration" id="duration" required>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="date">Date (leave blank to submit current date)</label>
              <input type="text" name="date" placeholder="YYYY-MM-DD" id="date">
            </div>
            <input type="submit" class="button" value="Submit">
          </form>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Retrieve Exercise Data</h2>
        <div class="subsection">
          <h3>Get the List of Users</h3>
          <p>To get the list of all the registered users, go to the route:</p>
          <pre><code>/api/exercise/users</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="subsection">
          <h3>Get Exercise Data for a User</h3>
          <p>To get data for a specific user, go to the route:</p>
          <pre><code>/api/exercise/log</code></pre>
          <p>and then add a parameter of the user's ID. For example, if I wanted to get the data for the user whose ID is <code>5bea63e40f02c48aab5f0e38</code>, I would go to the route:</p>
          <pre><code>/api/exercise/log/5bea63e40f02c48aab5f0e38</code></pre>
          <p>You can also filter the list of exercise logs that get returned. One method involves limiting the number of logs, such as:</p>
          <pre><code>/api/exercise/log/5bea63e40f02c48aab5f0e38?limit=2</code></pre>
          <p>You can also return logs that occur within a specific set of dates, such as:</p>
          <pre><code>/api/exercise/log/5bea63e40f02c48aab5f0e38?from=2013-10-31&to=2019-12-25</code></pre>
          <p>You can also both limit the number as well as select the date range, such as:</p>
          <pre><code>/api/exercise/log/5bea63e40f02c48aab5f0e38?from=2013-10-31&to=2019-12-25&limit=2</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
